<gtr:firstName>Caroline</gtr:firstName><gtr:otherNames>Alexandra</gtr:otherNames><gtr:surname>Chapain</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>CO_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole><gtr:personRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/47435899-86EA-431A-8C85-B193E199217C"><gtr:id>47435899-86EA-431A-8C85-B193E199217C</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>David</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Bailey</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole><gtr:personRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/7CF38A75-670F-4AD9-8BE9-B0F209A933FF"><gtr:id>7CF38A75-670F-4AD9-8BE9-B0F209A933FF</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Gill</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Bentley</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>CO_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FF024924%2F1"><gtr:id>9D8E2FFB-45B7-4F77-B8A7-335A301227AE</gtr:id><gtr:title>The Economic and Social Impact of the Demise of Rover at Longbridge: A Longitudinal and Holistic Approach to Economic Restructuring.</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Research Grant</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/F024924/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This project aims to understand how the loss of employment at Longbridge has affected the well-being of former MG Rover workers and their families, plus the impact on neighbourhoods. It examines the processes of adjustment and change, loss of job and subsequent work trajectories, the possible loss of income, health impacts, and the potential changes of address, school and travel to work patterns affecting ex-workers and their families, as well as the wider 'ripple effect' for their neighbourhoods.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>Specific objectives are:&lt;/p>

&lt;ol>
 

 &lt;li>To collate evidence related to the economic and social impacts of the closure;&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To use this evidence to evaluate the differential impact of change;&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To consider the role of community resilience through networks in minimising the impact of manufacturing decline;&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To evaluate agency intervention in dealing with the impacts of closure; and&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To contribute to the discussion of policy and practice around effective intervention and strategies for areas affected by manufacturing decline.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;p>The research will include a mix of quantitative and qualitative methods, with the main body of the research comprising a third wave survey of around 300 ex-Rover workers using the methodology and sample used by the Work Foundation in its 2006 report.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2009-04-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2007-11-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>79979</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>16E919AA-1754-4F2C-90E5-89518B466F60</gtr:id><gtr:title>Auto plant closures, policy responses and labour market outcomes: a comparison of MG Rover in the UK and Mitsubishi in Australia</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Policy Studies</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/042b3e90146043230abd551b4b579fc3"><gtr:id>042b3e90146043230abd551b4b579fc3</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Armstrong K</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2008-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>doi_53cf99f9915ddf0d</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>3F4A712B-70E3-4919-893C-B56AE2710BF5</gtr:id><gtr:title>Birmingham: whose urban renaissance? Regeneration as a response to economic restructuring</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Policy Studies</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/7